rComments: His accent makes the material bearable- the tests are beyond reasonable, and he's an all around funny, friendly guy. Would def take a course with him again. I was in a split with Copeland, you could tell when he wrote the exams. He was very fair. I did badly cause I was lazy. Coulda easily gotten an A. You can too!

Very passionate and exciting lecturer. Loves to help and has the best Australian accent. His examples in class are really  helpful when it comes to the exam. Make sure to read the textbook. Exams were tough if you don't study in advance. Try to read after the lectures and memorize things in chunks, other wise exams will be hard to study for.

He seems very nice, went really easy on us for the final exam. His teaching style might not be for everyone, he doesn't exactly follow the textbook and tends to digress but if you read the chapters at home - you'll be fine.
- pretty funny prof - lectures are long and covers a lot of material at the speed of light  - use slides  textbook - will eventually fall asleep, open youtbe9gag during lectures

Very nice guy, nice teaching style. read the textbook, but don't worry too much about remembering the stuff that isn't on his slides. go to class, take notes on the stuff he says, don't just memorize the slides. his voice can get a bit muffled, and his australian accent kind of makes it hard to understand, but manageable

Very interesting guy. His teaching style may not be for all but he definitely incorporates things into his lectures that make the sometimes otherwise boring material, very fun and enjoyable. Make sure you read up on what isn't thoroughly explained and listen to his stories (they're helpful for his midterms and exams) and you'll do well.

He always reminds students to do the reading and to study which is nice. There are a few times he tells us that a specific slide will be on the exam, but was not on the midterm... maybe it might be on the exam. His midterm is somewhat fair, other than some things he added that was unexpected. Study hard!
I found him to be an excellent, engaging lecturer who tells you STRAIGHT OFF that you need to be reading the textbook as well. I really enjoy his lecturing style and his experience stories.
He is such a bad teacher. Notes are horrible, you have to find what he's talking about in multiple chapters of the text book, which makes it very difficult to follow.
